BitBucket is similar to GitHub
senmar13/Sentmari07$
https://github.com/senmar13/git.git
Press Ctrl+Shift+P to access all VS commands
Open chat anytime with Ctrl+Alt+I
Ctrl+K Ctrl+T for theme settings (Dark mode/light mode)

git --version   ------ to know the git version
git config --global user.name 'senmar13@gmail.com' --> to config the user name
git config --global user.email 'senmar13@gmail.com' --> to config the user email
git config user.name --> to view the user name
git config user.email --> to view the user email
clear --> to clear the display console
git config --global init.defaultbranch main  --> config the default branch is main at initial time
git init --> intializing the empty git repository in D:/Git/.git/
Create files (like readme.md, index.html, index.js)
git status --> will display the untracked files created which is yet to add and commit in the main branch
git add readme.md --> to add the file in the repository for track
git commit -m 'readme' --> commiting the file for tracking
	[main (root-commit) e18b73a] readme --> e18b73a is commit id starts with(a hash value)
	1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)
	create mode 100644 readme.md
git log --> to view th details about when changes happened in the repository
git add . --> instead of each file add just mention . to add all files in main branch
git checkout e18b73a25b95e0c7a3b14dc8335b6f09954bba0b --> will go the version which is having the commit id
git checkout main --> again come back to current commit id which is points to main
git checkout -f main --> force to main checkout that recent changes without commit will be discarded.Only commited changes should be availble in main.
Ctrl+Shift+c  --> copy the content from terminal
right click --> paste
git remote add origin https://github.com/senmar13/git.git --> add the local git repository files to remote repository using the remote link
git branch -M main
git push --set-upstream origin main
git push -u origin main
git branch bug --> create a new branch with name 'bug' from current active branch
git checkout bug -->checkout the bug branch and switch to bug branch
git checkout -b feature --> instead of create and checkout a branch in two different steps, will do in single steps using this command
git branch new-bug bug --> i am in feature branch but i want to create a new branch 'new-bug' from bug branch
git push --set-upstream origin new-bug
git push -u origin feature --> Required only on first time for this branch
git push --> from next time just use this command to push the files to remote repository
- After push, we can do merge request from feature to main branch and delete the feature branch if not needed
git pull --> after select the main branch now, pull the merged code from remote main branch to local main branch
git fetch --> will fetch all the codes/branches from remote repository to local
git checkout new-feature --> branch 'new-feature' set up to track 'origin/new-feature' in local and Switched to a new branch 'new-feature'
Objective - new-bug changes has to be merged with main branch
shows conflicts
git checkout new-bug --> switch to new-bug branch
git merge main --> request for merge of main with new-bug
resolve conflicts
new-bug -> main merge
Resolve the conflicts
# Rename the current branch
git branch -m new-branch-name

# If renaming another branch
git branch -m old-branch-name new-branch-name

# Push the new branch and reset upstream
git push origin -u new-branch-name

# Delete the old branch from remote
git push origin --delete old-branch-name

# Move to previous commit id changes and discard the changes after that commit id
git reset commit id

unstaged - file got modified
staged - file changes accepted like git add filename
saved - file changes saved like git commit -m 'message'


